  <header class="article-header">
    <h1>A Who's Who of Latinos Wrote an Open Letter Denouncing Donald Trump</h1>
    <div class="by-line">
      <a title="Mathew Rodriguez's Profile" class="link-author avatar avatar-small" href="../../profiles/188907/mathew-rodriguez">
        <img alt="Mathew Rodriguez's avatar image" class="no-share-btns" src="http://media3.mic.com/NzY4YWYzOGQ5NCMvZHFBb2tqalpBZndQd1BXODZqMy1xbEtNQjQ0PS8yODh4OTI6NjQ1eDQ0OS8yNXgyNS9maWx0ZXJzOnF1YWxpdHkoODUpL2h0dHBzOi8vczMuYW1hem9uYXdzLmNvbS9wb2xpY3ltaWMtaW1hZ2VzL2YxNDgzOWZkYWNhYjFiNzU0NjRiMzY4NWFmMmE3YmQ3ZTNmZGNiZjhiN2M2MmI4MTkxZWI2ZmE2ODIyNWQxNmUuanBn.jpg">
      </a>
      By
      <a title="Mathew Rodriguez's Profile" class="link-author name" href="../../profiles/188907/mathew-rodriguez">Mathew Rodriguez</a>
      <time datetime="2015-11-07T20:18:34.000Z" pubdate="">November 07, 2015</time>
    </div>
    <div class="share-facebook-twitter subhead">
      <span class="fb-like-container-text">Like Mic on Facebook:</span>
      <span class="fb-button">
        <div class="fb-like-top fb-like" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/MicMedia" data-width="300" data-keen-tracking-name="subhed" data-keen-social-channel="facebook" data-show-faces="false" data-send="false" data-layout="button"></div>
      </span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div id="article-body" class="article-body share-media-toolbar-block"><div class="share-media share-media-side-fold">
  <ul><li class="share-media-facebook"><div class="share-button-count"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fmic.com%2Farticles%2F128109%2Fa-who-s-who-of-latinos-wrote-an-open-letter-denouncing-donald-trump" title="Share on Facebook" rel:gt_act="share/facebook/share" rel:gt_label="true" name="fb_share" target="_new" class="share-button share-button-medium-facebook modal-trigger-facebook k-trackable-share" data-fb-link="http://mic.com/articles/128109/a-who-s-who-of-latinos-wrote-an-open-letter-denouncing-donald-trump" data-keen-tracking-name="sidefold-share" data-keen-social-channel="facebook" data-popup-height="380" data-popup-width="660" data-facebook-pixel-id="6028307499936"><i class="social-icon-mini social-icon-mini-facebook"></i><i class="social-icon-divider"></i>SHARE</a></div></li>
<li class="share-media-twitter"><div class="share-button-count"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmic.com%2Farticles%2F128109%2Fa-who-s-who-of-latinos-wrote-an-open-letter-denouncing-donald-trump&amp;original_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fmic.com%2Farticles%2F128109%2Fa-who-s-who-of-latinos-wrote-an-open-letter-denouncing-donald-trump&amp;related=MicNews&amp;source=tweetbutton&amp;text=A%20Who's%20Who%20of%20Latinos%20Wrote%20an%20Open%20Letter%20Denouncing%20Donald%20Trump%20by%20%40mathewrodriguez&amp;via=MicNews" title="Share on Twitter" target="_new" class="share-button share-button-medium-twitter k-trackable-share" data-keen-tracking-name="sidefold-share" data-keen-social-channel="twitter" data-popup-height="380" data-popup-width="660" data-facebook-pixel-id="6028307499936"><i class="social-icon-mini social-icon-mini-twitter"></i><i class="social-icon-divider"></i>TWEET</a></div></li>
<li class="share-media-tumblr"><div class="share-button-count"><a href="http://tumblr.com/share/link?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmic.com%2Farticles%2F128109%2Fa-who-s-who-of-latinos-wrote-an-open-letter-denouncing-donald-trump&amp;description=He%20just%20got%20served%20%E2%80%94%20in%20another%20language.%20&amp;name=A%20Who's%20Who%20of%20Latinos%20Wrote%20an%20Open%20Letter%20Denouncing%20Donald%20Trump" title="Share on Tumblr" target="_new" class="share-button share-button-medium-tumblr k-trackable-share" data-keen-tracking-name="sidefold-share" data-keen-social-channel="tumblr" data-popup-width="450" data-popup-height="483" data-facebook-pixel-id="6028307499936"><i class="social-icon-mini social-icon-mini-tumblr"></i><i-social-icon-divider></i-social-icon-divider>POST</a></div></li></ul>
  <div class="corner"></div>
</div>
<div class="article-body-content"><p class="">Academy Award-winning actor Demián Bichir, actor Diego Luna, Academy Award-winning director Alejandro González Iñárritu and novelist Junot Díaz just dropped their latest collaboration. And no, they're not the stars, director and screenwriter of Hollywood's next hit.&nbsp;</p>
<p class="">These four, along with 63 other prominent Latinos from various fields including science, academia, the arts and law, wrote an open letter slamming Donald Trump. The letter, which&nbsp;<a href="http://www.univision.com/noticias/opinion/declaracion-de-intelectuales-cientificos-y-academicos-hispanos-contra-xenofobia-de-trump">Univision</a>&nbsp;published on Tuesday, decries "the verbal attacks of Mr. Trump are not based in statistics." All quotes are translated by<i>&nbsp;</i><i>Mic.</i>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="">The signatories wrote, "We condemn this attitude and we hope that the American people stop tolerating his absurd positions."&nbsp;</p>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small embeddable-image" id="embeddable-ie57atg" data-type="image"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://images.mic.com/ppwdqyo0iodgqy7hbz2za3yypirjvijbjh8a5avmbpgjmag04d8h6zia2ud5jd6i.jpg" alt="A Who's Who of Latinos Wrote an Open Letter Denouncing Donald Trump"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/donald-trump-attends-a-press-conference-for-the-release-of-news-photo/495547002" class="article-embeddable-source">Mic/Getty Images</a></figcaption></figure>
<p class="">People of various Latin and Latin-American backgrounds signed the letter, including prominent Mexicans, Chileans and Dominicans. Collectively, the letter's writers have won numerous awards, including the Nobel Prize and the Pulitzer Prize.&nbsp;</p>
<p>That the letter was published on Univision is no small irony, either. The Spanish-language <a href="http://mic.com/articles/121339/univision-shuts-down-donald-trump-s-anti-mexican-statements">TV station severed ties</a> with Trump and his Miss Universe competition after Trump's anti-immigration comments in June during his <a href="http://mic.com/articles/120785/best-quotes-from-donald-trumps-2016-presidential-announcement-speech#.gq2dPg5HN">presidential campaign announcement</a>. Trump also tossed respected <a href="http://mic.com/articles/121339/univision-shuts-down-donald-trump-s-anti-mexican-statements">Univision journalist Jorge Ramos</a> out of a press conference in August.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The letter denounced Trump's plans to deport millions of immigrants and build a wall on the U.S.-Mexico border.</p>
<p style="">"His hate speech appeals to the lowest passions, like xenophobia, machismo, political intolerance and religious dogmatism," the authors wrote. The letter said that Trump's anti-immigration sentiments are not new &mdash; in fact, past politicians who embraced these ideals are responsible for many deaths and physical assaults, the letter claims. The letter also pointed to the physical violence <a href="http://mic.com/articles/127315/watch-a-white-donald-trump-supporter-violently-throw-a-latino-protester-out-of-a-rally#.dYJPOxstS">Latinos have already faced</a> from Trump supporters.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="" class="">Puerto Rican singer Ricky Martin made similar points in an August op-ed posted on&nbsp;<i><a href="http://fusion.net/story/189517/ricky-martin-its-time-for-latinos-to-unite-against-donald-trump/">Fusion</a></i>.&nbsp;</p>
<figure contenteditable="false" class="embeddable clearfix image article-image-container article-image-container-horizontal photo embeddable-image-small embeddable-image" id="embeddable-99j9g5" data-type="image"><div class="embeddable-container"><img src="http://images.mic.com/bnz0b107m59ggh5hlbtd6dipyoie3i3pbhucl21xv2g55d3lp7c7o8hkaq8xxgl9.jpg" alt="A Who's Who of Latinos Wrote an Open Letter Denouncing Donald Trump"></div><figcaption class="article-embeddable-attribution">Source:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/ricky-martin-attends-the-the-paley-center-for-medias-news-photo/487882974" class="article-embeddable-source">Mic/Getty Images</a></figcaption></figure>
<p style="" class="">"We have to stop the power that Trump feels he has over Latinos, and the xenophobic speech that he and his campaign team seem to be convinced will be successful," Martin wrote.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="">The open letter also sees Trump's candidacy as a misstep for his campaign and the United States.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="" class="">In closing, they wrote, "Mr. Trump's behavior is unworthy of a candidate to the presidency of one of the most powerful countries in the world."</p></div>
